title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Create a plan that outputs all creditors that do not have "SLETTET" in their name, and that have an id between 193000 and 194000. Output in textfile.

title: Agent: SpecifierAgent Output
log: Select all creditors whose id is between 193000 and 194000 inclusive (id >= 193000 AND id <= 194000) and whose name does NOT contain the substring "SLETTET" (case-sensitive). Write the resulting records to a text file.

log.thoughts: The request filters creditors by creditor_id range and by name not containing 'SLETTET'. All required fields (creditor_id and name) are in the 'creditor' table, so only this table is necessary. No input text files are needed.

steps.detailed_description: Load the 'creditor' JDBC table with all columns (creditor_id, name, creditor_type) as the input dataset.

Filter the input dataset to keep only rows where creditor_id >= 193000 AND creditor_id <= 194000, and where the name does NOT contain the substring 'SLETTET' (case-sensitive). Input: full 'creditor' table. Output: filtered creditor records satisfying both conditions.
Write the resulting filtered creditor records (columns: creditor_id, name, creditor_type) to a text file (one record per line) as the final output.

log.thoughts: A simple pipeline: load the creditor table, apply the combined numeric range and substring-exclusion filter, then write the filtered records to a text file.

log.thoughts: Load the creditor JDBC table as the initial dataset. Start operator ids at 1 and expose all three columns for downstream steps.

log.thoughts: Load the creditor table (id=1) and apply a filter (id=2) keeping records with creditor_id in [193000,194000] and name not containing 'SLETTET'.
